The Spirit of the Lord then shall rest upon this branch; this branch which shall come forth from the stem and roots of Jesse by means of the Virgin Marty. And truly the Spirit of the Lord rested upon our Redeemer. It is written that "In hi dwells all the fullness of the Godhead bodily." The Spirit was not shed on Him by measure, as it is upon the Saints. To himw e may apply the words of the Hebrew Gospel used by the Nazarenes: "The whole fountain of the Holy Spirit shall be poured forth upon Him." Now the Lord is that Spirit, and where the Spirit of the Lord is, there is liberty.

